text:
Okay, so here's a weird one.
<http://2492639.hs-sites.com/resources>
I've got this resources page. This is a dynamic page, fed from HubDB. There are two tables, one which contains the resources themselves (thumbnails, titles, links, categories, and so on), and one which has some metadata for the "resource type" column on the other table. The page is dynamic based on the latter, so the subpages are like <http://2492639.hs-sites.com/resources/ebook-whitepapers> and <http://2492639.hs-sites.com/resources/case-study> (there are other filters, but those are just based on URL queries).
That all works fine, except for "webinars". The webinars page just 404's.
<http://2492639.hs-sites.com/resources/webinars>
The really weird part is, if we change the page path to anything else (even just "webinar" or "webinar-resources" or something), it _does_ work. it just doesn't like exactly "webinars". We can't find any redirects or page conflicts that would apply to this and I'm not sure what else to check. I can't think of a reason this wouldn't work. We'd like the url to be "webinars" if possible. Any ideas?

<@U3A4KEWK1|ianrmcnair> uploaded a file: <https://HubSpotdev.slack.com/files/ianrmcnair/F60E6SYUW/2017-06-26_13_14_09-edit_table___hubdb___HubSpot.png|2017-06-26 13_14_09-Edit table _ HubDB _ HubSpot.png>
Was just going to ask for that
The only thing I can think of is that "webinars" is a reserved url slug in HubSpot for some reason? I can't think of if I've ever made a page with that path in any portal.
hold on, Iâ€™m taking a look :slightly_smiling_face:
the fact that different slug variations of webinar work makes me think your guess is probably the case
especially if you can't find any redirects (but even a redirect wouldn't leave you on /webinars)
Right
is it the last row?
in that table
have you tried adding in a dummy row after it to see if there's an indexing issue
Yeah it is
I think I've tried that
is there actual webinar content
for that page?
Yeah that doesn't work
There is
Hmm
I was thinking it was like an empty blog
where it doesn't show up if there are no posts
Well I don't think it would matter if there were no webinars in the resources table
probably not
the template would render but with no content
just a thought
The dynamic page is based on the meta table, it doesn't really care what's in the other table
It would just show no resources
But there are webinars
And they show up when you change the path
I'm sure <@U22PJPGK0> will come up with some good reason it's failing. The weirdest thing for me is the path being different and working
Yeah
Turned out to be an archived page. D'oh
oh man
lol
It's still weird though because the url of that was actually /webinar, but we deleted it and now the page is there
Maybe /webinars was in the history of url slugs it still remembered that?
Whatever
at least next time you have a similar situation you'll know to troubleshoot via that route as well
Yeah
I had checked the "all pages" tab, but I guess archived pages don't show up on that
Which makes sense
